{"id": "duc04-testb-40:1#4", "contents": "The severity of North Korea's economic difficulties has been a subject of debate, with some visitors reporting that the food situation seems to be slightly better than a year or two ago. However, Hall's observations in rural areas, where foreigners are rarely allowed to visit, suggest that the overall situation is worse than ever. The United Nations has appealed for relief aid, but the latest appeal has raised less than one-third of the target. Aid agencies, including Doctors Without Borders, have also expressed concerns that their aid is not reaching the most needy due to the government's hard-line policies. As a result, ordinary North Koreans are suffering, with many children under the age of 2 acutely malnourished and physically stunted."}
